summary: Please take the time to consider joining the Crit Trash discord server! A server full of love, support, and dnd/critical role...
body:
Heyyooo it’s that time again!!

Please take the time to consider joining the Crit Trash discord server! A server full of love, support, and dnd/critical role content!

We are a majority 18+ (though there are a few between 14-17) friendly server, who are always looking for more people to talk to about our favorite, dumb, nerdy ass voice actors. We have custom emojis, fun color names, and silly commands to make live blogging an absolute chaotic mess.

We do have 100+ members but on average there is only about 20-40 members active and there are plenty of channels for you to talk in. We also have spoiler sections so those who are still catching up don’t have to fear being involved without having anything ruined for them.

Just click that link below and join today! We’d be ecstatic to have you! The server sends it’s persistent love to the critter community. May all your 20s be natural and have a very Critical Thursday!

Discord - Free voice and text chat for gamers

summary: What's your favourite one liner from each campaign?
question: What's your favourite one liner from each campaign?
answer:
I have such a terrible memory for specific quotes! It’s really a shame, because I know there are ones that I really loved in the moment, but I can’t every really pull them up when asked. Even if I could, my favorite lines/quotes are so tied into favorite moments that they don’t necessarily count as “one-liners.”

That said; Campaign 1: I deeply relate to Percy’s “You’re secret is safe with my indifference,” but my favorite ‘one-liner’ that I can actually remember is Vex’s “Take the mask off, darling.” Other favorite moments include Kerrek’s “passed through fire” letter, literally everything Sprigg said about life and death and stories, and Vax’s goodbye.

Campaign 2 is, weirdly, a bit harder. Does “Welcome to the Mighty Nein” count? Since it makes me cry literally every time someone says it? There’s “Shine bright, circus man,” for the tearjerking stinger on a moment through which I was already sobbing. Or “Case closed,” as the tearjerking stinger on an entire arc. Really just any time a character manages to reduce me to tears in ten words or less.
